secondary_outcome.description:
The rate of "low-risk" patients eligible for outpatient care:
HESTIA group: patients meeting none of the exclusion criteria of the rule (HESTIA rule negative);
sPESI group: patients with a simplified PESI score =0.

criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Admission to Emergency Department or unscheduled consultation in one of the
             participating centres;

          -  Symptomatic pulmonary embolism objectively confirmed according to the European Society
             of Cardiology criteria

          -  Insurance cover according to local legislation;

          -  Age ‚â•18 years;

          -  Free informed consent according to local legislation

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Shock or hypotension defined as systolic blood pressure <90 mmHg or a systolic
             pressure drop by ‚â•40 mmHg, for >15 minutes, if not caused by new-onset arrhythmia,
             hypovolaemia, or sepsis;

          -  Diagnosis of pulmonary embolism established more than 24H before inclusion;

          -  More than 48h between first presentation to the Emergency unit and inclusion - -
             Factors rendering 30-day follow-up impossible;
